// Japanese frequency-vocabulary word list (Word Bank, deepening pass
// 2026-07-13). Curated in-house — frequency-ranked by everyday usage, then
// assigned CEFR bands by rank. Tuple: [word, gloss, pos, tier, note?].
//
// Conventions (locked 2026-07-13):
// - word field packs script + romaji: "友達 (tomodachi)" — presented as-is,
//   no capitalization pass (cap() would be a no-op on the script and wrong
//   on the romaji). Kanji is used wherever it's the natural everyday
//   orthography, from A1 up — the romaji makes every entry readable, and
//   the Alphabet mode / script block teaches the writing systems themselves.
// - Romaji is macron-free wapuro Hepburn: arigatou, not arigatō.
// - The romaji parenthetical doubles as the intended-reading record for the
//   TTS pass — heteronym kanji (今日, 明日, 空) are disambiguated by it.
// - Verbs in dictionary form; na-adjectives listed bare (kantan, not
//   kantan na) with a note where the class is a trap (kirei, kirai).
// - pos: n (nouns), v (verbs), adj (i- AND na-adjectives — one distractor
//   pool; the na-class notes carry the distinction), adv, x (pronouns,
//   question words, greetings, set expressions).
// - Teaching notes are English-only, appended to the en explanation.

